    <p>This is an apt book for dis­cus­sion as World Men­tal Health Day, which falls on Oct 10, ap­proaches. All That Re­mains weaves the sto­ries of fam­i­lies touched by de­men­tia into a graphic novel. Com­mis­sioned by phil­an­thropic or­gan­i­sa­tion Lien Foun­da­tion, the book aims to foster pub­lic aware­ness and un­der­stand­ing and des­tig­ma­tise de­men­tia. Au­thor and comic artist James Tan is also be­hind Fi­nal Rest­ing Place, a graphic novel on the Bukit Brown ceme­tery. Part of Na­tional Li­brary Board’s SG Au­thor Se­ries in Oc­to­ber.</p>
    <p>WHEN: Oct 8, 8pm AD­MIS­SION: Free INFO: str.sg/JBER</p>


